  <summary>11/4/1999--Introduced.
Commercial Driver's License Devolution Act of 1999 - Amends Federal transportation law to allow an individual to operate a commercial motor vehicle for the transportation of property having a gross rating of up to 65,000 pounds solely within the borders of a State if such individual has passed written and driving tests meeting State-prescribed minimum standards.Provides penalties for the operation of a commercial motor vehicle in another State under a driver's license issued solely for operation within one State.</summary>
</bill>
